---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '@/components/Section.astro';
import LegalDocument from '@/components/LegalDocument.astro';

const supportEmail = 'arterasoftkoleksiyonum@gmail.com';
const title = 'Privacy Policy – Koleksiyonum';
const description =
  'Privacy Policy for the Koleksiyonum mobile app: what data we collect, how we use it, third-party services, retention, and your rights.';
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description} locale="en" htmlLang="en">
  <Section class="pt-24 sm:pt-28 md:pt-32">
    <LegalDocument
      title="Privacy Policy – Koleksiyonum"
      effectiveLabel="Effective Date"
      effectiveDateIso="2026-04-05"
      effectiveDateDisplay="April 5, 2026"
    >
      <p>
        Koleksiyonum (“we”, “our”, or “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains in
        detail how we collect, use, store, and delete your data when you use our mobile application.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>

      <h3>1.1 Account &amp; Identity Data</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Username and display name</li>
        <li>Authentication provider (email, Google, Apple)</li>
        <li>Password hash (for email-based accounts only)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.2 Profile Data (Optional)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>First name and last name</li>
        <li>Country and city</li>
        <li>Profile photo</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.3 User Content</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Messages between users</li>
        <li>Collections and saved products</li>
        <li>Favorites and notes</li>
        <li>Product links submitted by users</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.4 Product &amp; Interaction Data</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Product URLs and metadata</li>
        <li>Price history data</li>
        <li>Price alerts and tracking preferences</li>
        <li>User interaction events (app activity logs)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.5 Technical &amp; Device Data</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Device notification token (for push notifications)</li>
        <li>IP address and user-agent (for security and logging)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>1.6 Optional Metrics</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>User-provided metrics such as height, weight, or similar values</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <p>We use your data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Account creation and authentication</li>
        <li>Providing core application functionality</li>
        <li>Enabling social features (messaging, following)</li>
        <li>Sending notifications</li>
        <li>Improving performance and user experience</li>
        <li>Preventing abuse and ensuring security</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Data Sources</h2>
      <p>Some data displayed in the application is retrieved from third-party websites.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The application is not affiliated with these platforms</li>
        <li>Data is collected based on user-provided URLs</li>
        <li>Information may be incomplete, outdated, or inaccurate</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The application processes publicly available data only from user-provided links and does not claim ownership
        over such data.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We may use third-party services including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google Sign-In</li>
        <li>Apple Sign-In</li>
        <li>Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These services may process limited data necessary for authentication or notification delivery.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
      <p>Your data is stored securely and retained only as long as necessary.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Account data is retained while your account is active</li>
        <li>Logs and technical data may be retained for security purposes</li>
        <li>Cached and derived data may be stored temporarily for performance</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Personal data is retained while the account is active. Upon account deletion, data is removed or anonymized as
        soon as reasonably possible.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Account Deletion</h2>
      <p>You may delete your account directly within the application.</p>
      <p>Upon deletion:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Personal data is deleted or anonymized</li>
        <li>
          Associated user data (messages, collections, events, attributes, and related records) is permanently removed
        </li>
        <li>Certain system-level or aggregated data may remain where it cannot be linked back to you</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        After account deletion, personal data is deleted or irreversibly anonymized. Certain technical or aggregated data
        that cannot be linked back to the user may be retained for system integrity purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data. However, no system is
        completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>8. User Responsibilities</h2>
      <p>Users are responsible for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Content they upload or share</li>
        <li>Accuracy of submitted product links</li>
        <li>Compliance with applicable laws</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Third-Party Content Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        All product data, trademarks, and content belong to their respective owners. Koleksiyonum does not claim
        ownership of third-party content.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your data</li>
        <li>Request deletion</li>
        <li>Update your information</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>For any privacy-related inquiries:</p>
      <p>
        <a href={`mailto:${supportEmail}`}>{supportEmail}</a>
      </p>

      <h2>12. Updates</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy. Changes will be posted on this page.</p>
    </LegalDocument>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
